2026-03-29T16:38:41.8605330Z               "message": "Fix poll-build-logs skill: always poll when explicitly invoked\n\nPreviously the skill instructions told Claude to infer CI trigger rules\nfrom the workflow config and refuse to poll when it believed no build\nwould be triggered. This caused it to abort even when a PR existed.\nNow the skill always assumes a build is expected when explicitly invoked\nand only skips polling when a matching build already exists.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01QYf6BWVswoLZy5dhjW8hrR",
